# Pie Pastry

## Ingredients
* 100g Flour per person
* 50g Fat per person (butter|lard|suet)
* Salt
* Dried Thyme
* Ice-cold water
* Egg-wash|a little melted butter or milk

## Method
1. Form fine breadcrumbs with the first four ingredients, leaving relatively large pieces of fat covered in flour
2. Bring together with cold water
3. Kneed a little to form a shaggy dough (don't follow the general advice to not over work too religiously; it'll be just fine)
4. Refrigerate for 30 mins
5. Roll out and use, egg-washing top for best results

